      "title": "Secretaries appointed to 28 Ministries",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Sri Lankan Government published an Extraordinary Gazette dated the 26th of July 2022, declaring the appointment of 28 Secretaries to Ministries.",
        "2. M. M. P. K. Mayadunne \u2013 Ministry of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils and Local Government",
        "3. K. D. S. Ruwanchandra \u2013 Ministry of Ports, Shipping and Aviation",
        "4. S. T. Kodikara \u2013 Ministry of Trade, Commerce and Food Security",
        "6. Ms. Wasantha Perera \u2013 Ministry of Justice, Prison Affairs and Constitutional Reforms",
        "10. M. P. D. U, K. Mapa Pathirana \u2013 Ministry of Power and Energy",
        "12. H. K. D. W. M. N. B. Hapuhinna \u2013 Ministry of Women, Child Affairs and Social Empowerment",
        "18. Somarathna Vidanapathirana \u2013 Ministry of Buddhasasana, Religious and Cultural Affairs",
        "19. K. M. M. Siriwardana \u2013 Ministry of Finance, Economic Stabilization and National Policies",
        "21. B. L. A. J. Dharmakeerthi \u2013 Ministry of Plantation Industries",
        "22. R. M. C. M. Herath \u2013 Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Conservation",
        "24. P. H. C. Rathnayaka \u2013 Ministry of Urban Development and Housing",
        "25. R. P. A. Wimalaweera \u2013 Ministry of Labour and Foreign Employment",
        "26. Dr. Amal Harsha de Silva \u2013 Ministry of Sports and Youth Affairs",
        "Parliament to meet today (27); Emergency proclamation to be debated"
      ],
